    "title" : "Resultant Forces"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Determine the appropriate axes to be used during the resolution of forces.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Apply the appropriate sign conventions to indicate the directions of the force components.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Present the mathematical and graphical workings for solving problems involving resultant force vectors.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Deciding-the-Axes-to-Use",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Deciding the Axes to Use",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "The X and Y axes are perpendicular to each other",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "The X and Y components of the resultant force is non-negative (makes calculations easier)",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content" : [
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "If two forces are similar in magnitude and opposite in direction, use the cartesian",
                          "type" : "text"
                        },
                        {
                          "text" : " ",
                          "type" : "text"
                        },
                        {
                          "text" : "plane where positive Y is 90 degrees anticlockwise from the positive X axis",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "paragraph"
                    }
                  ],
                  "name" : "Exception",
                  "style" : "note",
                  "type" : "aside"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "One of the axes is parallel with the ground, ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "if the ground is sloped",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "emphasis"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "orderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The goal of choosing the correct axes are to avoid careless mistakes that arise from forgetting",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "negative signs or miscalculating angles.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Sign-Conventions",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Sign Conventions",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For an axis (eg. x-axis), forces which have a positive component in (ie. go in the same direction as)",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "the direction of the axis are positive numbers, and forces which have a negative component in (ie. go",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "in the opposite direction to) the direction of the axis are negative.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Mathematical-and-Graphical-Workings",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Mathematical and Graphical Workings",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "See ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/Notes\/documentation\/Notes\/Dynamics#2D-Force-Resolution",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " for how to resolve forces into their components, and what",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "workings to use.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
